### Rules
1. Each phase should be self-contained and independently executable
2. Phases should follow a logical dependency order (e.g., backend → frontend → integration)
3. Each phase should have clear inputs (from previous phases) and outputs (for subsequent phases)
4. Aim for 3-8 phases depending on complexity
5. The first phase should typically focus on foundational work (data models, core logic)
6. Later phases build on earlier ones
7. Each phase description should explain what decisions it makes and what artifacts it produces
